Subject to the provisions of this chapter and KRS Chapter 13A, the secretary shall, with the aid of his staff:
Attend all meetings of the board;
As provided by this chapter, promulgate comprehensive administrative regulations consistent with the provisions of KRS Chapters 13A and 18A, and with federal standards for the administration of a personnel system in the agencies of the state government receiving federal grants;
Establish general procedures for personnel recruitment, for certification, and for improving the efficiency of employed personnel;
Appoint the examiners and technicians necessary for the conduct of the personnel program, whether on a permanent or temporary basis;
Prepare and maintain a record of all employees, showing for each employee his name, address, title of position held, rate of compensation, changes in status, compensation, or title, transfer, and to make the data and the class specifications for all positions available to the press and public;
Prepare, in accordance with the provisions of KRS 18A.005 to 18A.200 and the administrative regulations adopted thereunder, examinations, eligible lists, and ratings of candidates for appointment;
Make certification for appointment or promotion within the classified service, in accordance with the provisions of KRS 18A.005 to 18A.200;
Make investigations concerning all matters touching the enforcement and effect of the provisions of KRS 18A.005 to 18A.200 and administrative regulations prescribed thereunder;
Prepare, in cooperation with appointing authorities and others, programs for employee training, safety, morale, work motivation, health, counseling, and welfare, and exercise leadership in the development of effective personnel administration within the several departments of the Commonwealth, and make available the facilities of the department to this end;
Provide personnel services to unclassified employees in agreement with the agencies involved not otherwise provided for in KRS 18A.005 to 18A.200;
Present, in accordance with the provisions of KRS Chapter 48, budget requests for the support of the personnel system created by KRS 18A.005 to 18A.200, excluding the board, which shall present its own budget estimates;
Make a report and submit the same to the board, the Legislative Research Commission, and the Governor not later than October first of each year;
Propose selection method changes for any classification to the Personnel Board with documentation justifying the need for the selection method change. The Personnel Board shall, at its next regularly scheduled monthly meeting, review and comment on any proposed selection method change. A classification shall not have its selection method changed without review and comment by the Personnel Board; and
Discharge the other duties imposed upon him by KRS 18A.005 to 18A.200.

The secretary shall establish and maintain a list of all filled positions exempted from classified service under KRS 18A.115(1) (e), (g), (h), (i), (k), (t), (w), (aa), and (ab). The list shall include the following information for each filled position:
The name of the agency where the position is assigned;
The statutory authority for the unclassified status of the position;
The title of the position;
The pay grade of the position;
The annual salary of the employee in the position; and
The work county of the employee in the position.
